This is recommended for most cases. If you want to hastily download a single video, the ', " guide below might be what you're looking for.", 'YouTube is the most popular video-sharing platform in the world and as a hacker, you may encounter a situation where you want to script something to download videos. For this, I present to you: ', '.', ' is a lightweight library written in Python. It has no third-party
dependencies and aims to be highly reliable.', ' also makes pipelining easy, allowing you to specify callback functions for different download events, such as  ', ' or ', '.', 'Furthermore, ', ' includes a command-line utility, allowing you to download videos right from the terminal.', 'This guide covers the most basic usage of the library. For more detailed information, please refer to ', '.', 'Pytube requires an installation of Python 3.6 or greater, as well as pip. (Pip is typically bundled with Python ', '.)', 'To install from PyPI with pip:', 'Sometimes, the PyPI release becomes slightly outdated. To install from the source with pip:', "To download a video using the library in a script, you'll need to import the YouTube class from the library and pass an argument of the video URL. From there, you can access the streams and download them.", 'Using the CLI is remarkably straightforward as well. To download a video at the highest progressive quality, you can use the following command:', 'You can also do the same for a playlist:', '
